<div class="dlp">
    <h1>NIAID Genomic Sequencing</h1>
    <section class="main">

        <div class="data-box">
            <h3 class="ribbon-title">The Genomic Centers for Infectious Diseases (GSCID)</h3>
            <p><a href="http://gsc.jcvi.org/" target="_blank"><img class="alignnone wp-image-3686" alt="J-craig-venter"
                                                                   src="/public/patric/images/J-craig-venter.jpeg"
                                                                   width="180" height="50"></a>
                &nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;
                <a href="http://www.broadinstitute.org/science/projects/gscid/genomic-sequencing-center-infectious-diseases"
                   target="_blank"><img class="alignnone  wp-image-3685" alt="Broad logo"
                                        src="/public/patric/images/Broad-logo-300x75.jpeg" width="208" height="53"></a>
                &nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;
                <a href="http://gscid.igs.umaryland.edu/"
                   target="_blank"><img class="alignnone wp-image-3684" alt="UMSM" src="/public/patric/images/UMSM.jpeg"
                                        width="223" height="59"></a>
            </p>
            <p>Many of the genomes and their metadata available at the BRCs come from the GCIDs. &nbsp; The GCIDs will
                use and develop or improve innovative applications of genomic technologies, such as RNA sequencing and
                metagenomics, and provide rapid and cost-efficient production of high-quality genome sequences of
                microorganisms, invertebrate vectors of infectious diseases, and hosts and host microbiomes related to
                <a href="http://www.niaid.nih.gov/topics/emerging/Pages/list.aspx"
                   target="_blank"> NIAID’s list of emerging and re-emerging infectious diseases</a>.</p>
            <p>For more information about projects conducted by the GCIDs, visit the individual Centers at</p>
            <ul>
                <li class="first">
                    <span style="text-decoration: underline;">
                        <a href="http://gsc.jcvi.org/"
                           target="_blank">The JCVI Genomic Center for Infectious Diseases</a></span>
                </li>
                <li><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><a
                        href="http://www.broadinstitute.org/science/projects/gscid/genomic-sequencing-center-infectious-diseases"
                        target="_blank">The Broad Institute Genomic Center for Infectious Diseases</a></span>
                    <ul>
                        <li class="last first"><a title="TB-ARC – TB Antibiotic Resistance Catalog"
                                                  href="/content/tb-arc-tb-antibiotic-resistance-catalog">TB Antibiotic
                            Resistance Catalog</a> (TB-ARC)
                        </li>
                    </ul>
                </li>
                <li class="last"><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><a
                        href="http://gscid.igs.umaryland.edu/index.php"
                        target="_blank">The Institute for Genome Sciences at the University of Maryland School of
                    Medicine</a></span>
                </li>
            </ul>
            <p>Several of the projects conducted by the GCIDs have a focus on antimicrobial resistance (AMR). &nbsp; A
                <a title="NIAID Antimicrobial Resistance Sequencing Projects"
                   href="/content/niaid-antimicrobial-resistance-sequencing-projects">consolidated
                    list</a> of these projects is available at PATRIC.</p>

